body:
## Steps to reproduce the issue

I encountered some problems when using the yosys to search the logic loop. When the logic loop consists of standard cells and user-defined cells, the "-all_cell_types" parameter seems to be normal. However, when the user-defined cells are not connected internally, The Yosys still incorrectly identifies the logic loop.

## Expected behavior
The logic loop can be correctly identified.
or How do I tell the difference between the two?


## Actual behavior
1、 a logic loop consists of standard cells and user-defined cells
```verilog
module TOP(input a,output b);

    wire d,c;
    assign d = a & c;

    TOP1 INST_TOP1(.x(d),.y(c));

endmodule


module TOP1(input x,output y);

    assign y = x;
    
endmodule

```
![case1](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/60563693/178867221-38eb20f9-ee70-48f4-a1cb-ce855f18cecf.PNG)

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/60563693/178868098-ab09c6a2-058a-44f8-9693-c09649912c03.png)
2、 a logic loop consists of standard cells and user-defined cells，but the user-defined cells are not connected internally
```verilog
module TOP(input a,output b);

    wire d,c;
    assign d = a & c;

    TOP1 INST_TOP1(.x(d),.y(c));

endmodule


module TOP1(input x,output y);


    
endmodule

```
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/60563693/178868378-8a740528-b084-469e-976e-c753378f5499.png)

